TITLE: Creating a Queue and Adding Jobs in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to import BullMQ, create a new queue, and add jobs to it asynchronously. It creates a queue named 'foo' and adds two jobs with different data payloads.
SOURCE: https://github.com/taskforcesh/bullmq/blob/master/docs/gitbook/README (1).md#2025-04-14_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Queue } from 'bullmq';

const myQueue = new Queue('foo');

async function addJobs() {
  await myQueue.add('myJobName', { foo: 'bar' });
  await myQueue.add('myJobName', { qux: 'baz' });
}

await addJobs();
```

