TITLE: Handling Worker Events in BullMQ with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to create a Worker and listen for 'drained', 'completed', and 'failed' events. These events are local to the worker that processed the jobs and provide job status information.
SOURCE: https://github.com/taskforcesh/bullmq/blob/master/docs/gitbook/guide/events/README.md#2025-04-14_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Worker } from 'bullmq';

const myWorker = new Worker('Paint');

myWorker.on('drained', () => {
  // Queue is drained, no more jobs left
});

myWorker.on('completed', (job: Job) => {
  // job has completed
});

myWorker.on('failed', (job: Job) => {
  // job has failed
});
```

