TITLE: Setting up a Worker to Process Jobs in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code sets up a worker to process jobs from the 'foo' queue. It uses IORedis for the connection and logs the job data. The worker will process jobs in the order they were added to the queue.
SOURCE: https://github.com/taskforcesh/bullmq/blob/master/docs/gitbook/README (1).md#2025-04-14_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Worker } from 'bullmq';
import IORedis from 'ioredis';

const connection = new IORedis({ maxRetriesPerRequest: null });

const worker = new Worker(
  'foo',
  async job => {
    // Will print { foo: 'bar'} for the first job
    // and { qux: 'baz' } for the second.
    console.log(job.data);
  },
  { connection },
);
```

