TITLE: Adding Multiple Job Trees Atomically with BullMQ FlowProducer
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to add multiple job trees atomically in a single operation using the FlowProducer's addBulk method. Each tree consists of a root job with child jobs, and the operation ensures that either all trees are added successfully or none at all, reducing Redis roundtrips.
SOURCE: https://github.com/taskforcesh/bullmq/blob/master/docs/gitbook/guide/flows/adding-bulks.md#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { FlowProducer } from 'bullmq';

const flow = new FlowProducer({ connection });

const trees = await flow.addBulk([
  {
    name: 'root-job-1',
    queueName: 'rootQueueName-1',
    data: {},
    children: [
      {
        name,
        data: { idx: 0, foo: 'bar' },
        queueName: 'childrenQueueName-1',
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    name: 'root-job-2',
    queueName: 'rootQueueName-2',
    data: {},
    children: [
      {
        name,
        data: { idx: 1, foo: 'baz' },
        queueName: 'childrenQueueName-2',
      },
    ],
  },
]);
```

