TITLE: Creating a Hierarchical Job Chain in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of creating a deeper job hierarchy where jobs depend on each other in a chain, allowing for sequential execution of jobs in a specific order.
SOURCE: https://github.com/taskforcesh/bullmq/blob/master/docs/gitbook/guide/flows/README.md#2025-04-14_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { FlowProducer } from 'bullmq';
const flowProducer = new FlowProducer();

const queueName = 'assembly-line';
const chain = await flowProducer.add({
  name: 'car',
  data: { step: 'engine' },
  queueName,
  children: [
    {
      name: 'car',
      data: { step: 'wheels' },
      queueName,
      children: [{ name: 'car', data: { step: 'chassis' }, queueName }],
    },
  ],
});
```

