TITLE: Implementing Manual Rate Limiting in BullMQ Worker
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to manually rate limit a queue based on external conditions like API responses. Uses the worker.rateLimit() method to dynamically apply rate limiting.
SOURCE: https://github.com/taskforcesh/bullmq/blob/master/docs/gitbook/guide/rate-limiting.md#2025-04-14_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Worker } from 'bullmq';

const worker = new Worker(
  'myQueue',
  async () => {
    const [isRateLimited, duration] = await doExternalCall();
    if (isRateLimited) {
      await worker.rateLimit(duration);
      // Do not forget to throw this special exception,
      // since we must differentiate this case from a failure
      // in order to move the job to wait again.
      throw Worker.RateLimitError();
    }
  },
  {
    connection,
    limiter: {
      max: 1,
      duration: 500,
    },
  },
);
```

