TITLE: Checking Group Rate Limit Status in BullMQ Pro
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to check if a group is currently rate limited using the getGroupRateLimitTtl method. Returns the time-to-live (TTL) of the rate limit for a specific group.
SOURCE: https://github.com/taskforcesh/bullmq/blob/master/docs/gitbook/bullmq-pro/groups/rate-limiting.md#2025-04-14_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { QueuePro } from '@taskforcesh/bullmq-pro';

const queue = new QueuePro('myQueue', { connection });
const groupId = '0';
const maxJobs = 100;

const ttl = await queue.getGroupRateLimitTtl(groupId, maxJobs);

if (ttl > 0) {
  console.log('Group is rate limited');
}
```

