TITLE: OpenTelemetry Consumer Instrumentation Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Configures OpenTelemetry SDK for the consumer service with OTLP exporters for traces and metrics.
SOURCE: https://github.com/taskforcesh/bullmq/blob/master/docs/gitbook/guide/telemetry/running-a-simple-example.md#2025-04-14_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { NodeSDK } from '@opentelemetry/sdk-node';
import { OTLPTraceExporter } from '@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-proto';
import { OTLPMetricExporter } from '@opentelemetry/exporter-metrics-otlp-proto';
import { PeriodicExportingMetricReader } from '@opentelemetry/sdk-metrics';

const sdk = new NodeSDK({
  serviceName: 'consumer',
  traceExporter: new OTLPTraceExporter({
    url: 'http://127.0.0.1:4318/v1/traces'
  }),
  metricReader: new PeriodicExportingMetricReader({
    exporter: new OTLPMetricExporter({
      url: 'http://127.0.0.1:4318/v1/metrics'
    }),
  }),
});

sdk.start();
```

