TITLE: Accessing Event Timestamp in QueueEvents Listener
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to access the timestamp of an event when using QueueEvents. It listens for the 'progress' event and logs the job ID, progress data, and the event timestamp.
SOURCE: https://github.com/taskforcesh/bullmq/blob/master/docs/gitbook/README (1).md#2025-04-14_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { QueueEvents } from 'bullmq';

const queueEvents = new QueueEvents("my-queue-name");

